F15- RULE ARMAGEDDON #

Each tribe will have to figure out 10 secret rules! These rules all vary in difficulty and how specific they are, however if there are any really specific rules, clues will be given at the start so it's not borderline impossible to solve. There will be two channels open for this challenge, one to submit your guesses and messages to be checked for in each rule, and the other to discuss what the rule could be. HOW GUESSING WORKS Every message your tribe sends in the submission channel will be checked if it does or does not follow the rule, every second message your tribe sends will get a chance to guess the rule, this repeats until the 10th message where your tribe guesses one more time. If you are all unable to guess correctly, then your tribe does not get a point for that rule. Make sure you notify staff whenever you submit a message or guess, ANY MESSAGES IN THIS CHANNEL COUNTS AS A SUBMISSION HOW DISCUSSION WORKS In the discussion channel and ONLY the discussion channel, you get to talk to the rest of your tribemates that are doing the challenge about what messages to submit and what the rule could b, DO NOT SUBMIT ANY ANSWERS IN THIS CHANNEL And if you’re still confused, then here's an example! ” i love muski”: CORRECT ”why did you make me do this help me please”: INCORRECT GUESS: Has to be less than 5 words: INCORRECT ”muski”: CORRECT ”jeff probst”: INCORRECT GUESS: Must contain the word Muski: INCORRECT ” i don't know what in the world this rule is”: INCORRECT ”slugs are cool”: CORRECT GUESS: Odd number of words: CORRECT Tribe who guesses the most amount of rules correctly wins!
7:33 AM
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- If its equal, then it’ll go down to number of guesses, fewest number of guesses win, if its a tie AGAIN, then it’ll be which tribe completed the challenge the fastest (we’ll remove any waiting time for hosts to show up and check the answers) Good luck!!

Pilot 4/26/2024 10:59 PM
Challenge will take the form of a 8 Question Quiz, with questions taken directly from the application. The questions used will be 1. “What name would you like to go by in the game?”, 2. “Do you have any ORG experience? (No experience is required) If so, please share.”, 3. “What's the craziest thing that has happened to you in recent memory?”, 4. “If you were a worm, would you still love me, and what would you do to show me that you still love me?”, 5. “How are you when it comes to challenges?”, 6. “What are your hopes and goals for this ORG? What would you most like to see?”, 7. “On one track there is a tiny baby, on the other track there are 5 ORG players. There is a speeding train headed towards the ORG players. Do you pull the lever to switch the train's track? Why?” 8. “What does a typical day in your life look life?” The players will have to match the jurors name to their answers The player will receive one point for each correct answer. 1 bonus point will be awarded if the player guesses all the answers right for a given player, and 1 bonus point will be awarded if the player guesses all the players right for an application question. This makes the max score 62. Tiebreaker will be time used to answer.

Pilot 7/13/2024 7:44 PM
Roborovski Roborovski enters the game storming hot, being the most active tribe of the three. On the first day, of the initial bonds, Austin, Shannon, and Gavino appeared to get the closest and voiced positive opinions about each other in their confessionals. Drock failed to notice that he had been cast on night 1 and did not end up showing up until halfway through day 2. Drock attempts to make up for it by quickly trying to align with Ghoody, but really makes progress after having a long voice call with Gavino. Shannon contributes a lot to the scavenger, making a very strong impression on her tribe, while Gavino makes a very strong impression strategically. Sunder communicates here and there, but is yet to form any strong relationships. Sokolov Jimbotron starts off even hotter than Roborovski, by going to every member of Sokolov and proposing an alliance. Every player accepts except for Edgy, who due to his extremely low activity is most likely the boot on this tribe. Jimbotron elects to choose Treb, Dinodan, and Kingofspades as his allies, creating the hamster headquarters alliance. The tribe all participates in the challenge, with Treb managing to contribute a significant amount and being generally beloved by his tribe.
7:44 PM
Long Tails: From the start, Robert takes issue with Horse for making a negative comment about Steven Universe during the cast reveal voice call, but he quickly gets over it as Robert, Eck, and Horse have formed a loose trio on this tribe. In the challenge, the team fails to work together as effectively as the other tribes. Eck and Robert attempt the most items, but fail to rally their teammates into contributing. Eck sits in voice call for most of the day, waiting for people to join to attempt items, but ends up spending almost the entire day alone in the tribe voice channel. Bunny ends up having her flight home from vacation canceled, and thus misses the first day. Due to jet lag, she neglects her one on ones, and fails to contribute items she said she would, and is voted out. However, though she is voted out without much discussion, multiple tribemates internally discuss preferring other votes, with Eck preferring to see Dicy go, and Dicy hoping to send Horse home. Marcille makes a fairly quiet showing, but ends up liked by the majority of the tribe. The idea of an Eck Robert Horse and a Dicy Marcille Robert alliance have both been subtly pitched, putting Robert in the middle should Long Tails go to tribal council again.

Extra Vote - Congratulations! You have found an extra vote! To use the extra vote, you’ll simply cast it in your submissions along with your regular vote before the voting deadline, allowing you to cast an additional vote at one tribal council. However, use of this extra vote comes with a catch. To be able to use this advantage, at the previous tribal council you must have voted for a player who was not eliminated. This advantage can last be used when there are 6 players left in the game. Extra Vote - Congratulations! You have found an extra vote! To use the extra vote, you’ll simply cast it in your submissions along with your regular vote before the voting deadline, allowing you to cast an additional vote at one tribal council. However, use of this extra vote comes with a catch. To be able to use this advantage, your vote must be cast for someone who is yet to receive votes at a previous tribal council. If you attempt to use this advantage on someone who has received votes at a previous tribal council, you will not be warned or made aware in your submissions, the vote will be read but not counted, and you will still lose the advantage. This advantage can last be used when there are 6 players left in the game. Extra Vote - Congratulations! You have found an extra vote! To use the extra vote, you’ll simply cast it in your submissions along with your regular vote before the voting deadline, allowing you to cast an additional vote at one tribal council. However, this extra vote comes with a catch. If a vote is cast against you and counted at tribal council, this advantage will be stolen from you and transferred to the player who voted for you. If multiple players voted for you, it will go to the first player to cast the vote in their submissions. This advantage can last be used when there are 6 players left in the game. This advantage is non-transferable except for the stealing mechanic. (edited)

In case I go to sleep and someone gets one, here's the descriptions of the 2 to offer Extra Vote - Congratulations! You have found an extra vote! To use the extra vote, you’ll simply cast it in your submissions along with your regular vote before the voting deadline, allowing you to cast an additional vote at one tribal council. However, use of this extra vote comes with a catch. To be able to use this advantage, your vote must be cast for someone who is yet to receive votes at a previous tribal council. If you attempt to use this advantage on someone who has received votes at a previous tribal council, you will not be warned or made aware in your submissions, the vote will be read but not counted, and you will still lose the advantage. 9:10 PM
Episode 3 - I gotta say I have nothing in the noggin (Eck) Roborovski On Roborovski, Drock fails to read the prompt properly and submits an invalid prompt, which initially puts him very much on the outs of his tribe, along with general inactivity. Gavino and Austin also very quickly m ake the first alliance of the tribe with Shannon. Shannon initially pushes Drock’s name, however, Gavino steps to his defense. Drock also goes overtime on the defensive, having a late night voice call with Shannon where he convinces her that Sunder needs to go, especially with an upcoming swap. Furthermore, the rest of the tribe gets annoyed with Sunder talking about his Jeopardy prowess, with Shannon especially talking about him being a challenge threat. In the meantime, Ghoody starts out rocky, by throwing out Gavino’s name to Drock, but then decides to create an alliance Austin and Gavino. In this, Ghoody reveals to them that he got the extra vote from the hamster cage. The tribe is also put off by Sunder’s anyone but me attitude, doubting his loyalty, and thus switches the vote off of Drock onto Sunder. Ghoody also proceeds to leak to Drock that the vote was initially on him. Sokolov Kingofspades tells Dinodan that he is his number 1, while Treb does the same, putting Dinodan in a power position. On top of that, Dinodan manages to open the hamster cage first, by guessing random four digit numbers indiscriminately. He tells Treb and Kingofspades, but lies about the stipulations to activate it, claiming that he needs to off-vote and receive a vote, rather than just off-vote, for reasons currently unknown. Depresso draws hamster versions of their entire tribe, and Jimbotron works with the other members of hamster headquarters to open the cage, but is too late.
9:11 PM
Long Tails : Following Robert turning down Horse’s alliance, and the start of the Dicy Eck Horse alliance, this tribe is a complete mess, with no one being able to agree on any sort of target. Robert and Marcille form a very close bond, and both decide that they won’t vote for each other. They choose to try and pull in Horse to vote out one of Dicy or Eck; Dicy for being generally untrusted, and Eck for his poor challenge performance. Meanwhile, Dicy and Eck contemplate who to vote out between Marcille and Robert. Horse decides that he doesn’t want to play the middle, and comes clean to Eck and Dicy about everything. He pins everything on Robert leading Horse and Dicy to target Robert, as Marcille is seen as just a follower. However, Eck decides that this is his opportunity to get in the middle, and proceeds to spend the day swapping his vote in his submissions between Dicy and Robert. He also tells Marcille that Robert will get blindsided and that he (Eck) is in the middle, but Marcille appears to not believe him.
9:11 PM
Hamster Cage The hamster cage hunt was 3 spread out hints, and a first come first serve advantage per tribe. The first person overall got to pick between 3 choices, the second got to pick between 2, and the last just got what was left. Dinodan solved it after the first hint, claiming an extra vote that he must vote incorrectly at the previous tribal to use. Treb and Depresso both solve it after the second hint, but as they are both Sokolov, they are unable to claim it. Ghoody then solves it next after the third hint, and claims an extra vote that can only be used on someone who has never received votes at a previous tribal council. Austin and Gavino both also end up solving it, but too slowly. Horse claims the last extra vote, which functions as normal, but is stolen from him by anyone who votes for him, beating out Eck by minutes. Robert also solves it later. Every player attempts the hunt except for Drock, Sunder, and Dicy (2 of whom went home, and all 3 got votes!)

Cwiara 7/31/2024 7:34 PM
Extra Vote - Congratulations! You have found an extra vote! To use the extra vote, you’ll simply cast it in your submissions along with your regular vote before the voting deadline, allowing you to cast an additional vote at one tribal council. However, this extra vote comes with a catch. If a vote is cast against you and counted at tribal council, this advantage will be stolen from you and transferred to the player who voted for you. If multiple players voted for you, it will go to the first player to cast the vote in their submissions. This advantage can last be used when there are 6 players left in the game. This advantage is non-transferable except for the stealing mechanic.
